sions by 95% by 2025 (Scope 1 & 2)\",\n    \"Offset remaining emissions through suitable measures\",\n    \"Achieve 25% reduction per customer in Scope 3 emissions by 2030\",\n    \"Achieve net-zero emissions by 2040 (Scope 1, 2, and 3)\",\n    \"Switch to e-mobility for the fleet: Published revised \u2018e-car-only car policy\u2019 in February 2022\",\n    \"Optimize energy efficiency in buildings: Using LED lighting, motion sensors, and reducing peak loads\",\n    \"Increase the use of renewable energy in buildings: Expanding photovoltaic systems and energy storage\",\n    \"Implement energy-efficient technologies in networks: Migrating to IP technology, removing 3G antennas, and improving energy management\",\n    \"Develop energy-autonomous cellular base stations\",\n    \"Double energy efficiency by 2024\",\n    \"Reduce CO\u2082"}
